Four persons were killed yesterday as security agencies repelled an attack by gunmen on the Ebonyi head office of the Nigerian Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA). The gunmen attacked the headquarters of the NDLEA located at Ntezi in Íshíelu local government area of the state around 2pm. It was gathered that the attackers, who came through the back fence of the facility, were later repelled by officials of the Agency alongside soldiers and police operatives.   Viral video: NYSC probes corpers’ erotic dance at camp     Residents, scavengers clash as FCTA demolishes shanties     BREAKING: APC Reps caucus endorses Tinubu for President   Police spokesperson, Loveth Odah confirmed the incident, saying that security agents killed two of the gunmen while others escaped. “Unfortunately, one of the officers and a patient undergoing rehabilitation at the Agency’s rehabilitation centre were also killed,” she said. The police spokesperson said two rifles and many rounds of ammunition were recovered from the attackers.